# Git — no implicit merge or push

- **Never** merge branches (`git merge`, PR merge, squash merge) unless the user **explicitly** asks.
- **Never push to GitHub** (any branch, including `main`) unless the user **explicitly** asks.
- **Never** push to `main` / `master` unless the user **explicitly** asks.
- Committing locally is OK when asked; default is **no push** until approved.
- If deploy needs `main`, tell the user and wait for approval — do not merge or push "to help."
